esent day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":81,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":90,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Roger De Knightley was born in 1134, in Knightley, Staffordshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1134–":"1134–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1134–Male":"1134–Surnud","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1134":"1134","1160":"1160","Knightley, Staffordshire,England":"Knightley, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1134–":"1134–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1134–Male":"1134–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1134":"1134","1160":"1160","Knightley, Staffordshire,England":"Knightley, Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"1134–":"1134–Décédé","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1134–Male":"1134–Décédé","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1134":"1134","1160":"1160","Knightley, Staffordshire,England":"Knightley, Staffordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Roger De Knightley e